  "text": "The characteristics of primary care management in these practices were obtained by a mailed survey instrument. Topics relevant to managing primary care were identified from our previous studies, from a literature review, and from focus groups. These focus groups comprised clinic and health plan medical directors and administrators. A survey of medical directors was developed to investigate the management of primary care in these practices. Many items were adapted from previous research. [CITATION_1] The care management techniques identified were demand management, referral management, hospital care management, physician profiling, and use of guidelines.",
